library(ggplot2)
library(maps)
world_map <- map_data("world")
ggplot(data, aes(map_id = country)) +
  geom_map(aes(fill = GDP.per.capita..constant.2015.US..), map = world_map) +
  expand_limits(x = world_map$long, y = world_map$lat) +
  labs(title = "World Map Chart - GDP per Capita (constant 2015 US$)")

ggplot(data, aes(x = country, y = Population..total)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "skyblue") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(title = "Population by Country", x = "Country", y = "Total Population")

ggplot(data, aes(x = Life.expectancy.at.birth..total..years., y = GDP.per.capita..constant.2015.US..)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color = "blue") +
  labs(title = "Life Expectancy vs. GDP per Capita", x = "Life Expectancy (years)", y = "GDP per Capita (constant 2015 US$)")

ggplot(data, aes(x = year, y = Military.expenditure....of.GDP.)) +
  geom_line(color = "red") +
  labs(title = "Military Expenditure as % of GDP Over Time", x = "Year", y = "Military Expenditure (% of GDP)")
